# {{LOOP_NAME}} — Human Gates & Budget

> A loop without human gates can act in ways no one intended.
> A loop without a budget can run forever. Both sections below are required.
> Do not mark the loop scaffolded if either is incomplete.

---

## Human gates

The following actions are **irreversible or high-blast-radius** and require
explicit human approval before the loop proceeds. The loop must halt at each
gate and wait for a clear "go" before continuing.

| # | Gate | Trigger condition | Who approves |
|---|------|-------------------|--------------|
| G1 | Pre-run sign-off | Before the very first live run on real data | Loop owner |
| G2 | Verifier anomaly | Verifier returns exit 1 on any iteration | Loop owner |
| G3 | Merge / apply | Before merging a branch or applying a patch to a protected target | Designated reviewer |
| G4 | Send / publish | Before sending a message, email, notification, or publishing content externally | Loop owner |
| G5 | Spend / bill | Before any action that incurs external cost (API call above threshold, cloud resource) | Budget owner |
| G6 | Delete / overwrite | Before deleting files, records, or overwriting data that cannot be recovered | Loop owner |

