### How to clear a gate

1. The loop writes a gate-request entry to `{{STATE_PATH}}` with the gate ID,
   reason, and proposed action.
2. A human reads the entry, confirms the action is safe, and replies with an
   explicit approval (a commit, a comment, a chat message — whatever the
   project convention is).
3. The loop reads the approval signal, records it in `{{STATE_PATH}}`, then
   continues.

Never self-approve. A loop must not treat its own output as a gate clearance.

